codex-switch
============

This project incorporates source code from the following third-party project:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

LearnPrompt/stepfun-codex-adapter
  Repository: https://github.com/LearnPrompt/stepfun-codex-adapter
  License:    MIT
  Used as:    src/adapter.py
              (extracted from install_stepfun_codex_adapter.sh PYADAPTER heredoc,
               see https://github.com/LearnPrompt/stepfun-codex-adapter/blob/main/install_stepfun_codex_adapter.sh)

The Python HTTP adapter that translates Codex Responses API requests into
OpenAI-compatible Chat Completions calls is the work of LearnPrompt and its
contributors, distributed under the MIT License. codex-switch redistributes
this code unmodified (or with only minor compatibility tweaks) and wraps it in
a GUI launcher and provider/key management system.

The original MIT copyright notice from upstream is preserved at the head of
src/adapter.py.

